Certainly! Below is a simple HTML file that allows you to upload an image, which will then be displayed scaled to 140x100 pixels without distortion. The image will maintain its aspect ratio, and any excess space will be filled with a background color.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Image Resizer</title>
    <style>
        body {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            height: 100vh;
            background-color: #f0f0f0;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        }
        #output {
            width: 140px;
            height: 100px;
            background-color: #ffffff;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            overflow: hidden;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
        }
        img {
            max-width: 100%;
            max-height: 100%;
            object-fit: contain; /* Maintain aspect ratio */
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <h1>Image Resizer</h1>
    <input type="file" id="fileInput" accept="image/*">
    <div id="output"></div>

    <script>
        const fileInput = document.getElementById('fileInput');
        const output = document.getElementById('output');

        fileInput.addEventListener('change', function(event) {
            const file = event.target.files[0];
            if (file) {
                const reader = new FileReader();
                reader.onload = function(e) {
                    output.innerHTML = `<img src="${e.target.result}" alt="Uploaded Image">`;
                }
                reader.readAsDataURL(file);
            } else {
                output.innerHTML = '';
            }
        });
    </script>

</body>
</html>
```

### How to Use:
1. Copy the above code into a text editor.
2. Save the file with a `.html` extension, for example, `image_resizer.html`.
3. Open the saved file in a web browser.
4. Use the file input to upload an image, and it will be displayed scaled to 140x100 pixels without distortion. The image will maintain its aspect ratio, and any empty space will be filled with a white background.
